Actually I missed something. It looks like the docstring cause this problem:
```python
import tvm

@tvm.hybrid.script
def test(input, output):
    """Docstring
    """
    batch_size = input.shape[0]
    num_anchors = input.shape[1]
    elem_length = input.shape[2]
    for i in range(batch_size):
        valid_idx = 0
        for j in range(num_anchors):
            if input[i, j, 0] >= 0:
                for k in range(elem_length):
                    output[i, valid_idx, k] = input[i, j, k]
                valid_idx = valid_idx + 1

if __name__ == '__main__':
    a = tvm.placeholder((1, 5000, 6), name="a")
    b = tvm.placeholder((1, 5000, 6), name="b")
    c = tvm.hybrid.parse(test, [a, b])
```
If I remove docstring, it works fine.

